HOME ASSISTANT – MQTT ASSIGNMENT REPORT

Name: Giridharan S
Register Number: 42110367

MQTT Topic Used:
home/Giridharan-2025/sensor

Description of Additional Sensor:
A simulated ambient light sensor was added to demonstrate how multiple data points can be transmitted over MQTT. It sends a constant lux value, serving as an example of how Home Assistant can process and display readings from an extra sensor such as light intensity.

Summary of Procedures Completed

Set up Home Assistant OS on VirtualBox
Home Assistant was deployed in a virtual environment on a Windows system using Oracle VirtualBox.

Installed and configured the Mosquitto MQTT Broker on Windows
The Mosquitto service was set up as the MQTT broker and prepared to accept messages from external clients.

Developed a Python script to publish sensor readings
A Python client was created to send temperature, humidity, and the custom light-sensor values to the designated MQTT topic.

Integrated MQTT into Home Assistant
Home Assistant’s MQTT integration was configured to listen to the published topic, enabling communication between the broker and the dashboard.

Verified sensor updates on the Home Assistant dashboard
All three sensor values were successfully received and displayed in real time within the Home Assistant interface, confirming correct end-to-end MQTT communication.
